{"_id":"EQUPsgHAi0rSVZz6","name":"1:Dungeon Level","content":"<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ffb9ae1d-7fff-a2ea-31ab-a5eb1558f47a\"></span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong>Well Room: </strong>has secret door, we know how to open and close it now. Also has hay on the floor and shields along the wall (probably it has been searched thoroughly but maybe we should look to see if anyone has hidden anything here?). Message written in Elvish on the walls: \"<em>Beyond the Pillar forest, the Mad Mage waits. Casting spells behind magic gates.</em>\"</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong>Demon Hallway: </strong>Demon carvings along the entry hallway - Secret door to the south pointed to by skeleton (can't open yet). Another secret door we can open goes north.<br /><br /></span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong>Pillars:</strong> there is a note that says, &ldquo;Certain death lies this way&rdquo; and points south. Fought bugbears with intellect devourers in their heads. Weird giant snake skeleton. Found a secret compartment that had been cleaned out in one pillar.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong>Bone Pillars</strong>: Fought some grell. No loot.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong>Armor and Sword: </strong> Magical sword and skeletal remains of a hand. Almost definitely cursed. Probably in such a way that you either immediately lose your hand or you have to cut your own hand off. Connects to Demon Hallway through secret door.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong>Three Statues: </strong>Was held by the Undertakers (all dead), several entrances including a secret one behind a cupboard. There was a </span><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">white-wooden staff with a stupid alarm spell on it. Why even note it here? Giffzak is angry about the whole ordeal.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Undertakers:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> This is where the Undertakers were hanging out. There's a dwarven fresco on the north wall where Boot found a hidden key in a dwarf's eye, there's also a tub inset into the floor below the fresco, finally there was a small cache of coins (about 90 gp total).</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Stinky Crap Hole:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> The room is filled with nasty sewage that gets deeper as the room slants downwards to the west. A sahaguin statue glows a faint purple and is missing an arm with it's head twisted around. The statue's head can be screwed off and there is a compartment inside that holds melted wax. We found the corroded arm in the filth. We were attacked by some kind of ooze (grey?) and killed it.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong>Mirrored Hall: </strong>16 Mirrors line the hallway, radiating illusion magic of some kind. There is a burnt out torch in the hallway.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Dungeon Campsite:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> This looks like an abandoned campsite where adventurers have stopped in the past. We didn't find anything here but it might be a good place to take a short rest.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Shattered Statue/Goblin Party Hall/Gobby Stank</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">: There was a group of bugbears and goblins hanging out in this area. The goblins were playing with a skeleton chanting \"Nimwraith.\" Zak found and repaired a broken shield with the name Nimwraith. We killed most of the goblins and the survivors fled. The statue was once three warriors.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Wild Magic Gate: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">A broken archway that holds some form of wild magic. A goblin got pushed through by a bugbear when Yrsinia was watching and nothing happened. When Boot passed through he turned invisible. When Zak went through he took 27 damage. Ash decided not to go through.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Talk to Me:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> A weird skeleton missing it's legs was here. There was a message written in infernal nearby that says, \"Talk to Me.\" We talked to it in Infernal and Common. Somewhat predictably, it didn't respond.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Mined Hall: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">A dead goblin with some digging tools was found in this hallway connecting two areas of the dungeon. The goblinoid faction must have done it for some reason.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Sexy Lady:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> A headless statue of a woman with a cobra head found nearby. There are a disturbing number of monster based statues in this dungeon...</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Sexy Dude:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> There is a fat naked guy playing a lute (or something) here. We still need to do more investigation. I think there was a severed 10 foot pole as well. Not sure what that means. There is a message around the frame that says, \"Gaze upon me with bronzed visage, and secrets shall I reveal.\"</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Wizard Mirror:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> There is a big mirror with a wizard built into the frame. A strange and haunting melody can be heard as we approach. Heard a girl's voice telling us we can't pass through this mirror yet. Her name was Jhesiyra Kestellharp. The portal looks like it goes to lower levels.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Fine Fellow in a Pit:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> An undead adventurer (Halath) was abandoned here by his peers, at least that's his story. He seems to be trapped in the pit and has asked to get out. He also reavealed that there is a secret door nearby. There is a relief carved into the wall with 23 levels of the dungeon in Undermountain. Each level is specially illustrated. The 3rd level shows flaming skull, the 16th shows a comet, and the 23rd level shows a tower with a tiny rune.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Bugbear Room:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Maybe part of the goblinoid faction (with intellect devourers) we've come across before. 3 bugbears and a handful of goblins, all dead now.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Bloody</span><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Obelisk: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">A great stone obelisk that was worshipped by the goblins. Touching it gives the message, <em>\"I cast my eye into the future and see in yours a perilous descent. South of here, beyond a secret passage, waits the Two-Headed King. Look to his left. There you will see the path you are destined to take.\" </em>Path down to the second level? Secret trap door to south of obelisk. </span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Grick Lair: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">We fought and killed a handful of grick. No loot.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong>Two-Headed King: </strong>The statue is life-size and depicts a dwarf king standing atop a 3-foot-high stone pedestal. Sprouting from the king's neck is a deformed, mostly featureless second head with an elongated, toothless mouth. The inscriptions on the pedestal have been worn away. On the king's brow rests an engraved stone circlet, and his large hands grasp the handle of a stone warhammer, the head of which is planted at his feet. Found a magic circlet under the statue by rotating the hammer.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Ettin'</span><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">s</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong> Forge</strong>: A large forge, some dead carrior crawlers, and some loot. Stored at the back of the forge are two large sacks. One sack contains 1,400 cp and 350 sp. The other contains 120 iron ingots worth 5 sp each. Each ingot weighs 1 pound and is stamped with a hammer on one side and an anvil on the other. We through all the loot into Ash's bag of holding.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Elven Hall: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">There were some elven statues in here including one with a golden spear. That one was a mimic. We killed it so hard.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">We looked</span><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> up: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">There were a ton of stirges in here but we took them out with prejudice. There was a crack in the roof that leads to the surface somewhere but we have a better way to get up.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Wererat's</span><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Den</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Lots of wererats. Flindol = boss. We garnered an agreement to leave any rats/wererats we find alive, and free them from the clutches of Xanathar's Guild. Met another wererat a little down the hall and she went to go meet up with Flindol and the others. No real need to kill them I guess. Although that has rarely stopped us in the past. Down the hall we also found a secret passage leading to the Hall of the Winds.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Hall of the</span><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Winds: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">We fought an Air Elemental (the first time Boot has taken damage!). After beating the elemental we took a short rest here and Boot had a quick conversation with a few other goblins and gave them instructions on how to find a giant grick skull to keep as a souvenir. There was also some random trash items laying around but I didn't write down what they were.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Storerooms:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Just some random storerooms with a dried up skeleton. We found hide armor and an oak staff but they didn't seem magical.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Its a CAAAAVE:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Weirdly carved room to look like a cave. There's a really nice bath. We all finally got the sewer gunk off. Ash watched us all bathe. He's weird like that.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Gelatinous Maze: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Suspiciously clean hallways made Ash and Boot adopt the \"shoot first, ask questions later\" approach. There was a gelatinous cube. We killed it.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Totally a</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong> Vampire</strong>: A suspicous tomb with holy water inside. We left it alone but Yrsinia broke the vial.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Get</span><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Buried:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> More members of the Undertakers. A handful of bandits, a doppleganger, the leader of this group \"Haria\" and a flesh golem. The flesh golem walloped on us but we killed 'em all. There was a huge bone throne to look at a little more but we did get like 20 gold, so... yay? There was also an odd bone throne in here. The throne is trapped with magical serpents that are really nasty.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Armor Pile:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> An ancient pile of armor? Does it animate? What kind of armor is it?</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Six</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong> Pillars</strong>: The pillars are pockmarked up and down the length of the hall. Check for traps.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Human Statues and Dead Spiders:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Lots of statues facing inwards and spiders killed by crossbow bolts. Probably killed by the Undertakers. It doesn't seem like the statues have traps.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong>Copper Throne</strong>: Put on a copper helm, sit on the throne, out pops a <em>Wand of Secrets</em>. </span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong>Fishy Heart</strong>: Well-made Sahuagin statue with magically suspended blob of liquid above it. Secret box in statue (made of lead) holds a dry heart full of cursed necromatic magic. Curse removed by Boot, and swallowed by Yrsinia. </span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Manticore Den:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Killed three manticores. We found some loot (a chain shirt, a flail, a wooden flute (2 gp), a pouch containing 14 sp and 29 cp, a pouch containing 21 gp, and a silver necklace with a bloodstone pendant worth 250 gp). Good fight.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Trollhome:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> There WAS a troll living here and eating some random meat. There is now a dead troll who is lying next to some meat.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Bloody Mess:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Weird random bloody tables with fresh blood but no bodies. Find out that meat magically appears here to feed troll and Manticores.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Ancient Dining</span><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Hall: </span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">We found a copper tankard under the table worth 25 gp. Ash wants to check to see if it's magical. It wasn't</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Dead</span><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Adventurer:</span></strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Holding a tin flagon, a backpack was nearby. Burgler's pack missing a lantern and a flask of oil.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"color: #191813; font-family: Arial; font-size: 16px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong>Vault of the Basilisk</strong>: Black Pudding protecting one statue. Stone dead adventurers.</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Factions:</span></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 13.999999999999998pt; font-family: Arial; color: #434343; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Undertakers</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">A group of vampires who charge gold for passage (50 gp)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The doorkeeper of the territory is named Amvis</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">We totally killed them. They were actually bandits and a doppleganger and a guy named Uktarl Krannoc.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">There was a second leader, Haria that we found a little later. She's dead too. Somehow she controlled a flesh golem though.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 13.999999999999998pt; font-family: Arial; color: #434343; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The Fine Fellows</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">A group of adventurers that came into the Undermountain looking for treasure. The group members were Halath, a priest of Waukeen; Rex, a human fighter; Copper Stormforge, a dwarf; Midna, a priestess of Shar; and Kaleem, the scout. The scout was trapped by Gricks and has returned to the surface. Halath was killed by his Fine Fellows, came back as an undead, and wants his revenge. We are going to help. Fun.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 13.999999999999998pt; font-family: Arial; color: #434343; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Xanathar's Guild</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">It looks like the bugbears, goblins, and intellect devourers are all working for Xanathar. Not sure why they are here but we've killed boatloads of them. There were also some wererats loosely connected to Xanathar (see Cult of Raxivort below)</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 13.999999999999998pt; font-family: Arial; color: #434343; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Cult of Raxivort</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">A group of wererats that were being forced to serve Xanathar before we killed all of Xanathar's minions on the first level. They now seem to be independant agents working on their own. Their leader is Flindol.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Monsters:</span></h2>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Bugbears with Intellect Devourers</span></li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Goblins</span></li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Grell</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Fake Vampires (bandits)</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Doppelganger</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Grey Ooze</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Grick</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Ettins</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Stirges</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Wererats/Rats?</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Air Elemental</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Gelatinous Cube</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Flesh Golem</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Manticores</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Troll</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; color: #191813; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Black Pudding</span></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","img":null,"folder":"QqiLFziZrLtjZFs7","sort":100000,"permission":{"default":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Foreword","permission":{"default":-1,"ZjdmMWEyMmE2NzVk":3},"folder":"xU2zPB5VIEAHK3ql","sort":100001,"flags":{},"content":"<div class=\"w-100 overflow-x-hidden\"><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--0\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--0\" data-title-index=\"300\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Foreword</span></span> <p><div class=\"float-clear\"></div><div class=\"\"><div class=\"rd__wrp-image\">\n\t\t\t<a href=\"https://5e.tools/img/adventure/WDH/Cover.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" title=\"In Waterdeep, a gold coin is called a dragon, and someone has hidden half a million dragons in the City of Splendors. Tyler Jacobson illustrates the villains hunting for the treasure. May the gods protect any adventurer who stands in their way!\">\n\t\t\t\t<img class=\"rd__image\" src=\"https://5e.tools/img/adventure/WDH/Cover.jpg\"   >\n\t\t\t</a>\n\t\t</div><div class=\"rd__image-title\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"rd__image-title-inner \">In Waterdeep, a gold coin is called a dragon, and someone has hidden half a million dragons in the City of Splendors. Tyler Jacobson illustrates the villains hunting for the treasure. May the gods protect any adventurer who stands in their way!</div>\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t</div></div></p><p>A simple question began rattling around in my head over two years ago as I was bidding farewell to Barovia, dragging myself out of the depths of Maelstrom, and planning a yearlong expedition to Chult. Where do we go next? After mulling over several options, we decided it would be refreshing to return to civilization. Waterdeep: Dragon Heist is a treasure hunt with an urban backdrop. We've visited Waterdeep before, but not like this. Clever heroes will respect the city's rules. Those who get on the city's bad side are in for a rough time, as the City of Splendors is home to some of the most powerful figures in the Forgotten Realms.</p><p>Charlie Sanders, a lifelong D&D player, brought his experience writing for television to the project by helping flesh out the story bible months before work on the adventure was scheduled to begin. Matthew Mercer, whom you might know from the livestreamed show {<i>Critical Role</i>}, lent us his boundless imagination and helped flesh out the villains and their motives. A D&D adventure is only as good as its villains, and Waterdeep: Dragon Heist has multiple baddies to choose from.</p><p>Before I pull back the curtain and lead you into the heart of Waterdeep, I wish to thank Ed Greenwood for making the City of Splendors what it is: the kind of magical place you wish in your heart was real.</p><p>{<b>Chris Perkins</b>} December 2017</p><div  class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" data-title-index=\"301\" > <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Pronunciation Guide</span></span> <table class=\" striped-odd\"><thead><tr><th class=\"col-6\" data-rd-isroller=\"false\" >Name</th><th class=\"col-6\" data-rd-isroller=\"false\" >Pronunciation</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class=\"col-6\"  >Agorn Fuoco</td><td class=\"col-6\"  >AY-gorn foo-OH-koh</td></tr><tr><td class=\"col-6\"  >Ahghairon</td><td class=\"col-6\"  >ah-GAIR-awn</td></tr><tr><td class=\"col-6\"  >Ahmaergo</td><td class=\"col-6\"  >ah-MAIR-go</td></tr><tr><td class=\"col-6\"  >Alcedor Kolat</td><td class=\"col-6\"  >awl-SEE-door KOH-lat</td></tr><tr><td class=\"col-6\"  >Alturiak (month)</td><td class=\"col-6\"  >awl-TUR-ee-ak</td></tr><tr><td class=\"col-6\"  >Amath Sercent</td><td class=\"col-6\"  >AH-math SER-sent</td></tr><tr><td class=\"col-6\"  >Ammalia Cassalanter</td><td class=\"col-6\"  >ah-MAW-lee-ah KAS-ah-lan-ter</td></tr><tr><td class=\"col-6\"  >Arn Xalrondar</td><td class=\"col-6\"  >ARN zal-RON-dar</td></tr><tr><td class=\"col-6\"  >Aurinax</td><td class=\"col-6\"  >OR-ah-nax</td></tr><tr><td class=\"col-6\"  >Avareen Windrivver</td><td class=\"col-6\"  >ah-vah-REEN</td></tr><tr><td class=\"col-6\"  >Bregan D'aerthe</td><td class=\"col-6\"  >BRAY-gan DAIRTH</td></tr><tr><td class=\"col-6\