{"_id":"NDYxZDUwNWZkYjEw","name":"Handout: Mezzoloth","permission":{"default":2},"folder":"Y2FjMmQ1NTRiMzZl","sort":1000000,"flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":100,"handout-archived":false}},"content":"","img":"modules/dotmm-shared/journal/028_-_Player_Handouts/001_-_Creatures__26_Monsters/100_-_Handout_3A_Mezzoloth/avatar.png"}
{"_id":"NDZhZTk0MTVkYzEw","name":"Level 7: Maddgoth's Castle","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"ZWE1ODJjMzhjZjAz","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":0,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":0,"entryTime":0,"content":"\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p></p><h2>Level 7: Maddgoth’s Castle</h2>Maddgoth’s Castle is designed for four 9th-level characters, who should amass enough XP to reach 10th level. The characters can forge tenuous alliances with several of the monsters on this level. Award XP for these creatures as if the characters had defeated them in combat.<p></p><p>The level is named after a miniature, one-twelfth-scale fortress in one of its caverns. This castle serves as the home base of Madd­goth, a serial killer who lures other wizards to his lair to murder them and keep their arcane focuses and spellbooks as trophies. Madd­goth isn’t home when the adventurers first arrive, but he might show up later (see <a class=\"entity-link\" data-entity=JournalEntry data-id=ZDQyMjFlYjMwNGZl ><i class=\"fas fa-book-open\"></i>Aftermath</a>). Most creatures are reduced to one-twelfth their normal size as they approach Maddgoth’s castle, enabling them to better fit inside. Either by design or because of some failing, the shrinking magic doesn’t affect all creatures, as adventurers who explore the castle will discover.<br></p></section>","img":"modules/dotmm-shared/journal/008_-_Level_7_3A_Maddgoth_27s_Castle/000_-_Level_7_3A_Maddgoth_27s_Castle/avatar.png"}
