{"_id":"NjBhZmRmMDUwOWM4","name":"Savaros","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"NjU5NDE4YmRkMmQ0","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":8,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":80000,"entryTime":0,"content":"<h1>Savaros</h1><p><i>Elder Rune of Goblinkind</i></p><p><br></p><p><b>Bane Effect:</b> All nonmagical coins and gems on the target’s person vanish.</p><p><b>Boon Effect:</b> The rune magically summons a goblin (use the goblin stat block in the <i>Monster Manual</i>), which appears in an unoccupied space within 20 feet of the target. The goblin is rude to everyone except the target and obeys the target’s commands. The goblin vanishes in a puff of smoke if it drops to 0 hit points.</p><div><br></div>","img":"modules/dotmm-shared/journal/031_-_Elder_Runes_Deck_Handouts/008_-_Savaros/avatar.png"}
{"_id":"NjEwYjE5NWNkYzhj","name":"Headband of Intellect","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"ZDVkNGI3NGVkMTk0","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":35,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":350000,"entryTime":0,"content":"<h4>Headband of Intellect</h4><p><i>Wondrous item, uncommon (requires attunement)</i><br></p><p>Your Intelligence score is 19 while you wear this headband. It has no effect on you if your Intelligence is already 19 or higher without it.<br></p>\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p><br></p></section>","img":"modules/dotmm-shared/journal/029_-_Magic_Items/035_-_Headband_of_Intellect/avatar_1.png"}
{"_id":"NjEzOGRkMWU2MWU4","name":"Quicksand","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"ZTAwZjhmZTU5ZGU5","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":10,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":100000,"entryTime":0,"content":"\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p>A quicksand pit covers the ground in roughly a 10-footsquare area and is usually 10 feet deep. When a creature enters the area, it sinks 1d4+1 feet into the quicksand and becomes restrained. At the start of each of the creature’s turns, it sinks another 1d4 feet. As long as the creature isn’t completely submerged in quicksand, it can escape by using its action and succeeding on a Strength check. The DC is 10 plus the number of feet the creature has sunk into the quicksand. A creature that is completely submerged in quicksand can’t breathe (see the <a href=\"https://roll20.net/compendium/dnd5e/Rules:The%20Environment?expansion=0#content\">suffocation rules</a>).</p><p>A creature can pull another creature within its reach out of a quicksand pit by using its action and succeeding on a Strength check. The DC is 5 plus the number of feet the target creature has sunk into the quicksand.</p></section>","img":""}
{"_id":"NjIyN2NhODQxZWEz","name":"Oil of Slipperiness","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"ZDVkNGI3NGVkMTk0","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":49,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":490000,"entryTime":0,"content":"<h4>Oil of Slipperiness</h4><p><i>Potion, uncommon</i><br></p><p>This sticky black unguent is thick and heavy in the container, but it flows quickly when poured. The oil can cover a Medium or smaller creature, along with the equipment it's wearing and carrying (one additional vial is required for each size category above Medium). Applying the oil takes 10 minutes. The affected creature then gains the effect of a <i><a class=\"entity-link\" data-entity=Item data-id=MmU0NGI5ZjhlMWE3 ><i class=\"fas fa-suitcase\"></i>freedom of movement</a></i> spell for 8 hours.<br><br>Alternatively, the oil can be poured on the ground as an action, where it covers a 10-foot square, duplicating the effect of the <i><a class=\"entity-link\" data-entity=Item data-id=NjNmMDg4ZjQ2NWI0 ><i class=\"fas fa-suitcase\"></i>grease</a></i> spell in that area for 8 hours.<br></p>","img":""}
