{"_id":"NmNmMDczMTU3NTdh","name":"Level 8: Slitherswamp","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"M2FiNjZlNjRhOTlk","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":0,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":0,"entryTime":0,"content":"\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p><h2>Level 8: Slitherswamp</h2><p>Slitherswamp is designed for four 10th-level characters, and characters who defeat the monsters on this level should gain enough XP to reach halfway to 11th level. This level consists of muck-filled caverns and decaying temples dedicated to evil deities of the yuan-ti. The serpent folk lived here until they were defeated by nagas known as the Ssethian Scourges. Afterward, Halaster replaced the yuan-ti with a bullywug tribe governed by a cruel death slaad overlord.</p></p></section>","img":"modules/dotmm-shared/journal/009_-_Level_8_3A_Slitherswamp/000_-_Level_8_3A_Slitherswamp/avatar.png"}
{"_id":"NmQ0NGM5MjM1MGM0","name":"Handout: Flameskull","permission":{"default":2},"folder":"Y2FjMmQ1NTRiMzZl","sort":520000,"flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":52,"handout-archived":false}},"content":"","img":"modules/dotmm-shared/journal/028_-_Player_Handouts/001_-_Creatures__26_Monsters/052_-_Handout_3A_Flameskull/avatar.png"}
{"_id":"NmQ0YzA4YjdkNTA4","name":"Immortal Insanity","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"MDU0YWU4MzFmMTE1","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":11,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":110000,"entryTime":0,"content":"<h1>Immortal Insanity</h1><p>The Mad Mage of Undermountain has destroyed himself or been destroyed many times, but his demise is always short-lived. Folk say the dungeon cannot exist without him, and so it magically re-creates the archmage whenever he meets his end within its crumbling halls. Each time Halaster returns, less of his sanity remains.</p><div><br></div>","img":"modules/dotmm-shared/journal/032_-_Secrets_Deck_Handouts/011_-_Immortal_Insanity/avatar.png"}
