{"_id":"ODhlNmI3MGJiYzBi","name":"Elemental Gem (Air)","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"ZDVkNGI3NGVkMTk0","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":27,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":270000,"entryTime":0,"content":"<h4 style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\">Elemental Gem (Air)</h4><p style=\"color: rgb( 64 , 64 , 64 )\"><i>Wondrous item, uncommon</i><br></p><p style=\"color: rgb( 64 , 64 , 64 )\">When you use an action to break the gem, an air elemental is summoned as if you had cast the <i><a class=\"entity-link\" data-entity=Item data-id=NDM4ZWRlNzY1MWU1 ><i class=\"fas fa-suitcase\"></i>Conjure Elemental</a> </i>spell, and the gem's magic is lost.</p>","img":"modules/dotmm-shared/journal/029_-_Magic_Items/027_-_Elemental_Gem__28Air_29/avatar_1.png"}
{"_id":"ODk1MTZhYjc4MThi","name":"Wand of Secrets","permission":{"default":1},"folder":"ZDVkNGI3NGVkMTk0","sort":860000,"flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":86,"handout-archived":false}},"content":"<h4>Wand of Secrets</h4><p><i>Wand, uncommon</i><br></p><p>The wand has 3 charges. While holding it, you can use an action to expend 1 of its charges, and if a secret door or trap is within 30 feet of you, the wand pulses and points at the one nearest to you. The wand regains 1d3 expended charges daily at dawn.<br></p>\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p><br></p></section>","img":"modules/dotmm-shared/journal/029_-_Magic_Items/086_-_Wand_of_Secrets/avatar_1.png"}
{"_id":"ODkwMjJiNGViMTZh","name":"Ullathar","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"NjU5NDE4YmRkMmQ0","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":9,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":90000,"entryTime":0,"content":"<h1>Ullathar</h1><p><i>Elder Rune of Passage</i></p><p><br></p><p><b>Bane Effect:</b> The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be restrained for 24 hours.</p><p><b>Boon Effect:</b> For the next 24 hours, the target gains the following benefits:</p><ul><li>The effects of the <i>freedom of movement</i> spell</li><li>The ability to cast the <i>knock</i> spell at will, requiring no components</li></ul><div><br></div>","img":"modules/dotmm-shared/journal/031_-_Elder_Runes_Deck_Handouts/009_-_Ullathar/avatar.png"}
{"_id":"ODljNDExYjVhNzE3","name":"Elemental Ooze","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"NDNkZGIzOWM4Zjdi","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":3,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":30000,"entryTime":0,"content":"\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><h2>Elemental Ooze</h2><p>The orb in area 4 weeps a steady stream of ooze channeled from the Swamp of Oblivion, the border realm between the Elemental Planes of Earth and Water. This ooze is a thick, viscid brown effluvium with streaks of orange, green, yellow, and black. It smells like rotten eggs and sticks to anything it touches. The ooze is never more than 5 feet deep in any given location and is difficult terrain. It moves slowly in the direction indicated by the wavy arrows on map 19 and also behaves like it’s alive, occasionally extruding harmless pseudopods or amorphous shapes that bear passing resemblances to familiar creatures.<br></p></section>","img":""}
{"_id":"OGFjOTg5MjQ5NjA0","name":"Battle Map Scale","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"ODAwNDU4MjE1ODdh","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":2,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":20000,"entryTime":0,"content":"\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p></p><p></p><p>Listed below are all the maps in this module and what scale they are currently set at. </p><hr><h3 style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\">5 Foot Maps (Half-Unit)<br></h3>Each grid square was 10' on the original art, however they have been adjusted to 5' on the Roll20 grid (<strong>Grid Size</strong>&nbsp;set to&nbsp;<strong>0.5</strong>&nbsp;units and&nbsp;<strong>Map Scale</strong>&nbsp;set to <strong>10</strong> feet). No adjustments are needed for tactical accuracy.<p></p><p></p><strong>All maps in <i>Dungeon of the Mad Mage</i> are to this scale.</strong><br><h3 style=\"font-family: &#34;helvetica neue&#34; , &#34;helvetica&#34; , &#34;arial&#34; , sans-serif\"><br></h3><p></p><p></p></section>","img":""}
