{"_id":"OWViNzMxMzdiYzQx","name":"Potion of Fire Breath","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"MzEwZWQwN2I5NTYw","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":5,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":50000,"entryTime":0,"content":"<h4>Potion of Fire Breath</h4><p><i>Potion, uncommon</i><br></p><p>After drinking this potion, you can use a bonus action to exhale fire at a target within 30 feet of you. The target must make a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw, taking 4d6 fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. The effect ends after you exhale the fire three times or when 1 hour has passed. This potion's orange liquid flickers, and smoke fills the top of the container and wafts out whenever it is opened.<br></p>\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p><p><br></p></section>","img":""}
